// Java program to check whether the given number is an Armstrong or not.

package armstrongnumber;
public class ArmstrongNumber {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int n=153;int sum=0;
        String s=Integer.toString(n);
        double len=s.length();
        int temp=n;
        while(temp>0){
            double res=0;
            res=temp%10;
            //res=;
            sum+=Math.pow(res, len);
            temp=temp/10;
        }
        if(sum==n)
            System.out.println("The given number "+n+" is an Armstrong Number.");
        else
            System.out.println("The given number "+n+" is 'NOT' an Armstrong Number.");
    }
}

OUTPUT:

The given number 153 is an Armstrong Number.
